status: MARC21-007: Secondary support material of nonprojected graphic
Type of material (other than normal museum matting) to which the primary support is attached.

definition (en): Fine, smooth pasteboard used by artists and painters.
Man-made substances other than textiles, plastic, and vinyl.

scope note (en): Includes all natural or synthetic fibre fabrics except canvas.

definition (en): Secondary support material varies for different items in a collection.
Fine-grained unsplit lambskin, kidskin, or calfskin prepared especially for writing or drawing on.

scope note (en): Includes mixtures of ground solids and plaster.

definition (en): Material that is based on wood particles or fibers may or may not be considered wood.
Secondary support material is not known.
Skin of a sheep or goat prepared for writing on.

Secondary support material other than canvas, bristol board, cardboard/illustration board, glass, synthetic, skin, textile, metal, vinyl, plastic, mixed collection, vellum, paper, plaster, hardboard, porcelain, stone, wood, leather, parchment.
